	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Besides correcting some dark spots in the map and moving some enemies, plus changing and adjusting a few bits, as suggested, I've changed the way the game starts.<br /><br />I wish this makes learning the basic gameplay dynamics easier and the game more intuitive.<br /><br />First of all, every interactuable spot where you can press &quot;B&quot; comes with a nice bouncing arrow, so the first thing you see when you start a new game is this:<br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<img src="./download/file.php?id=8102" alt="image_2017-02-24_14-02-08.png" /><br />
			<span class="gensmall">image_2017-02-24_14-02-08.png [ 10.13 KiB | Viewed 2373 times ]</span>
		

		<br />
	</div><br />(the arrow only appears when you actually can interact. For example, it won't appear over teleporters if you don't have enough charges). <br /><br />Once you use the pedestal and recharge your powers, cheril says something. Just this once, of course:<br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<img src="./download/file.php?id=8103" alt="image_2017-02-24_13-32-45.png" /><br />
			<span class="gensmall">image_2017-02-24_13-32-45.png [ 10.53 KiB | Viewed 2373 times ]</span>
		

		<br />
	</div><br /><br />The balloon won't go away until your activate your powers, and you need to do so to actually start the game.<br /><br />I have a couple more things to polish before I can post a new (definitive) version. Just wanted to know what you guys think about the changes.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
